<hr><font face="sans serif,arial,helvetica" color="000000" size="5"><b>Using the lists</b></font><br><br><br>


<b>The objects’ lists are a useful alternative to the explorer window. They allow you to
see information and navigate through the data. Lists are extremely easy to manage.
Here are the options offered:</b><br><ol>
<li>Change the columns’ order by dragging and dropping.<br><br></li>
<li>Display or hide any column: although, you can not remove or hide the last
column. The default list of columns (also called fields) can be defined for a
specific list. If no selection is made, all possible fields will be displayed.
Columns can be added via a pop-up menu, which you will find on top of the
table.<br><br></li>
<li>Sort Ascending or Sort Descending any column; click the column’s name.
The sorted order will be indicated by a triangle pointing upward or downward
as well as a color gradation (from pale to dark for ascending order).<br><br></li>
<li>Resize the columns’ length.<br><br></li>
<li>Save each lists’ setting separately.<br><br></li>
<li>Set, via the pop-up menu, the horizontal and vertical lines display.<br><br></li>
<li>Access pop-up menus by right-clicking an object in the list.<br><br></li></ol>

<b>You can display the lists in three ways:</b><br><ol>
<li>In the <b>main menu</b> select <b>Display</b> > <b>List</b> > the <b><i>object</i></b> you want to have
listed.<br><br></li>
<li>In the <b>toolbar</b>, choose the <b>List tool</b> <img src="../images/TOOL_list.jpg"> and the <b><i>object</i></b> you want to have
listed.<br><br></li>
<li>From the <b>explorer</b> or the <b>diagram</b> window, <b>select the object</b> you want to
have listed by <b>right-clicking</b> it and from the <b>pop-up menu</b> choose <b>List</b>.<br><br></li></ol>
<b>The lists allow numerous viewing and browsing options. And if you wish to edit an
object:</b><br><ul>
<li>Select it from the list and easily edit it via the design panel.<br><br></li>
<li>Right-click this object and choose properties (or click the properties tool in
the navigation toolbar).<br><br></li></ul>
<b>Lists are extremely useful to display and browse through the numerous
objects of your project.</b>
<br><br>


